To run tests, simply enter the command `pytest` into the terminal window.

All scripts starting with "test_" will be executed and all functions starting with 
"test_" will be run.

To only run a specific test module contained in <filename>, use the command 
`pytest <filename>`

To only run a specific test, use the command `pytest <filename>::<testname>`

To show how much time each test takes, use the `--duration=0` option
